</tr></td></table><P><br />
Now, to some of you, this is just a mass of non-sensical text/numbering. Unfortunately, to those of us that play in VT, this is a nightmare. <br />
<br />
Somehow, VT on Veeshan is COMPLETELY bugged (I mean bugged more than normal). Warders are not disappearing when they are supposed to, people are going linkdead for no apparent reason, and worst of all, mobs are receiving UNPRECEDENTED hit points and regenative abilities.<br />
<br />
The mob represented in the chart is what we call an Aten Blob, one of two. This Blob had, at our best estimates, around 10,000,000 hit points. The damage shown in the chart above was just MELEE damage over a period of 1:39 minutes. That's right folks - a mob that usually takes 20-30 minutes to kill -MAX- took 66 Fires of Heaven members one hour and thirty nine minutes to kill. <br />
<br />
After we killed the Blob, we went to test out the other side to see if his brother was also bugged. Boy were we unpleasantly surprised to see the answer was 'YEP!' Needless to say, we called the raid and everyone left in disgust.<br />
<br />
Why do I make this post here?<br />
<br />
A few reasons. Firstly, when I petitioned one of the Super Smart Verant GMs about bugged warders, their response was that they cannot respawn or mess with the spawn of any warders after the Sleeper had been released. OK!? <br />
<br />
Secondly, I've never fought anything for almost two hours straight... wait for it... I have heard of mobs in PoP having up to and maybe beyond ten million hit points. Let me just say that if any single boss encounter ever lasts this long again in any expansion, I can guarantee you people at Verant that everyone that aspires to reach this level of gaming in Everquest and everyone thats already at this level will leave. I would rather play Minesweeper while a rabid chimp gnaws at my testicles than go through another fight like the one we had yesterday. Nobody that I know that participated disagrees with me, and if anybody else ever has to go through this, I assure you they will feel the same way.<br />
<br />
With Much Love,<br />
<br />
Furor</font>
			
